parse: Verb - Present Indicative Active - 1st Person Singular
str2: (a) I say, speak; I mean, mention, tell, (b) I call, name, especially in the pass., (c) I tell, command.
A primary particle; down, in varied relations (genitive, dative or accusative) with which it is joined).
Poverty, want, need. A falling short, i.e., penury.
For. A primary particle; properly, assigning a reason.

parse: Personal / Possessive Pronoun - Nominative 1st Person Singular
str2: I, the first-person pronoun. A primary pronoun of the first person I.

parse: Verb - Aorist Indicative Active - 1st Person Singular
str2: Prolongation from a primary verb, another form of which, matheo, is used as an alternate in certain tenses; to learn.
I am, exist. The first person singular present indicative; a prolonged form of a primary and defective verb; I exist.
Self-sufficient, contented, satisfied, independent. From autos and arkeo; self-complacent, i.e. Contented.
In, on, among. A primary preposition denoting position, and instrumentality, i.e. A relation of rest; 'in, ' at, on, by, etc.
